<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in the Philippines (
                        McNutt
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d684</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">684</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-07-15T21:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-07-15T21:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-15T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="684" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.36/7–1646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Philippines</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McNutt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Manila</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-16T10:00:00+08:00">July 16, 1946—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 16—6:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. Draft treaty<note n="61" xml:id="d684fn1">Of friendship, commerce, and
                        navigation.</note> informally presented with warning many changes necessary.
                    Philippine Govt not yet organized for detailed discussion formal negotiations.
                    Hope begin by August 1 if changes mentioned your telegram received.<note n="62" xml:id="d684fn2">In telegram 91, July 24, 1 p.m., to Manila, the Department
                        sent a change and added: “Since <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                        anticipates need to propose changes in draft from time to time, opening of
                        discussions with Philippine Govt need not be delayed pending receipt of
                        additional amendments.” (711.96/7–1646)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McNutt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
